task.summary: Default task
Clearer names for functions to detect optional and array property schema
Add saved JSON points of comparison from classic implementation in a test resource directory.
Add missing fdlLink alias for fdl_link parameter
Supply no-arg constructor values for Clip's tracker, timing, lens, and static (and all static's component) parameters
Remove class docstring for StaticCamera; clear out unused import and a dead TODO
Incomplete push towards matching schema
wrapping classic camdkit schema as with pydantic-style Optional works
Add missing units on capture frame rate and shutter angle
Improve description newline normalization; place units alongside descriptions; be explicit with JsonSchemaValue
Add missing "captuure_frame_rate" clip_property to definition of StaticCamera's capture_frame_rate field.
Add missing millimeter units on nominal focal length
Use up-to-date name 'distortionIsProjection'
Add JsonSchemaMode argument (defaulting to 'validation') to make_json_schema; add anyOf flattening via model_field_schema of generator; canonicalize_descriptions name change
Regression utility to load classic schema. Static schemas for camera, lens, tracker all match
Remove redundant check in generator's model_field_schema method
Much cleaner removal of default and nullable layers when serializing, via improved model_field_schema() method
Add missing units to Lens fields
Better model_field_schema, but not done
Incomplete progress towards passing all unit tests, especially those of schema equivalence
Add some extracted JSON from classic camdkit against which to test
More progress towards schema equality
And yet more progress towards schema equality
Match proposed typo, docstring cleanup in PR to classic camdkit
Correct expected docstring for TimecodeFormat
Use json_schema_extra to express in the generated JSON schema that one of focus, zoom or iris is required.
Spelling fix in lens docstring.
Reflect fix in lens docstring in lens.json; other spelling and newline fixes in lens.json.
Make focus distance a strictly positive real.
Introduce a Distortions type, that groups together Distortion objects of different models. The clip now has a field that is a tuple of Distortions, not a tuple of tuples of Distortion.
Add units to generated schema when making comparisons; in the normal context of generating Clip schema, they would be there, but in isolation they aren't generated.
Add STRICTLY_POSITIVE_REAL constraint string.
Use harness setUpModule and tearDownModule to read reference schema just once.
Add maximum values for raw encoders.
Remove unused exception object from except statement.
Don't throw away outer min_length or max_length when pulling next layer up through trapdoor

Perform surgery on deepcopy'd core schema rather than the one passed in to model_field_schema. Until this change, running individual unit tests in a file might all succeed, but running the file as a whole might fail.
Remove some commented-out debugging code and more precisely type JSON schema value.
Remove some commented-out debugging code and more precisely type JSON schema value.
Focus distance JSON reference now contains exclusiveMinimum for zero, not minimum.
Updated Poetry and PyCharm infrastructure files.
Updated implementation notes
Fix clip_property for tracker notes and type spec for both notes and rcording
Add missing clip_property for duration
A variety of changes to get to where generated documentation passes and all other unit tests pass as well.
IDE changes
IDE changes in support of documentation match.
Rearrange directory structure to match camdkit.

Rearrange directory structure to match camdkit.
